examples: Turn the cloth over so that the patterned side is up .

definitions.definition: On or at a physically higher level.
examples: The flood waters are up again across large areas of the country.

definitions.definition: Headed or designated to go upward (as an escalator , stairway , elevator etc.) or toward (as a run-up ).
examples: Where is the up escalator?

definitions.definition: Fitted or fixed at a high or relatively high position, especially on a wall or ceiling.
examples: All the notices are up now.
The Christmas decorations are up .

definitions.definition: Available to view or use; made public; posted.
examples: Is your new video up yet? I looked on the website, but I couldn't find it.
The kite is up !
The castle drawbridge was up .
Don't go into the living room just now – I've got the carpet up .
Are the new buildings up yet?
The audience were up and on their feet.
I can’t believe it’s 3 a.m. and you’re still up .

definitions.definition: Above the horizon , in the sky.
examples: It'll get warmer once the sun's up .

definitions.definition: Larger; greater in quantity , volume, value etc.
examples: Sales are up compared to last quarter.
My temperature is up this morning.

definitions.definition: Indicating a larger or higher quantity.
examples: The barometer is up , so fine weather should be on the way.
The home team were up by two goals at half-time.
Time is up !
Her contract is up next month, so it's time to negotiate another one.
I’m feeling up today.
If you are up for a trip, let’s go.
labels: usually in the phrase up for
definitions.label_groups: usually in the phrase up for

examples: Smith is up to bat.

definitions.definition: Happening; new ; of concern. See also what's up , what's up with .
examples: What's up , bro?
What is up with that project at headquarters?
When I saw his face, I knew something was up .

definitions.definition: Said of the higher-ranking pair in a two pair .

examples: I’m not up on the latest news. What’s going on?
Is the server back up ?
The London train is on the up line.
labels: of a railway line or train
definitions.label_groups: of a railway line or train

examples: Would you like that drink up or on ice?

definitions.definition: Erect . (Can we add an example for this sense?)
